# Text selectability

The app uses `user-select: none` and `cursor: default` globally on `<body>` so all UI chrome (headers, labels, nav items, buttons, badges, status tags) is non-selectable with a normal pointer — matching native desktop app behavior.

## When to add `select-text cursor-text`

Add `select-text cursor-text` to elements that display **user data** someone might want to copy:

- Package names, filenames, `.var` references
- Creator / author names (when displayed as plain text, not as a clickable link)
- Version strings
- File paths, directory paths
- Error messages, stack traces, scan results
- URLs
- Toast message text
- App version / build info strings

## When NOT to add it

Leave the global non-selectable default for:

- Section headers, labels, descriptions, help text
- Button text, nav items, tab labels
- Status tags (Installed, DEP, Direct, Missing, etc.)
- Badge text, counts in UI chrome
- Filter labels, sort options
- Empty-state messages

## Inside clickable containers

For text inside clickable cards or table rows (where the whole row/card has an `onClick`), prefer keeping data selectable in the **detail panel** rather than on the card itself — adding `select-text` inside click targets can create UX friction between click and drag-to-select.

## Pattern

```jsx
{/* Non-selectable by default — no extra classes needed */}
<h2>Section Header</h2>

{/* Copyable user data */}
<span className="select-text cursor-text">{pkg.filename}</span>
<div className="select-text cursor-text">{error.message}</div>
```
